      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REMUS PHOENIX (11) has done a terrific job to place behind superstar mare Keayang Zahara in Group 1 races in his last two outings, one here and the latest at Menangle. Draws on the back row but came from there to score at this circuit and distance three back. Strong claims with even luck. I AM WILMA (1) is building in fitness and has the hoof on the till after finishing second in all three starts since a spell. Won the Vicbred 3F final at this circuit and distance last season. Tackles the boys but should get her chance from the ace draw. LOVEMETO NZ (9) broke last time but beat REMUS PHOENIX when second in the G1 Grand Prix here two back and he has only once missed a place in 10 tries at this distance, winning four of them. QUIRKY CHARACTER (6) continued his consistent form when placed last start. Owns a strong record here and deserves respect again as does PINNIE (3) who beat him home when winning last week.",
